# Testing Requirements

Comprehensive testing standards across all layers.

This rule defines quality gates and test scope. For workflow guidance on how to
write tests during implementation, follow `test-driven-development.mdc`.

## Hard Requirements

- Do: test all major layers (unit, component, integration, API/model).
- Do not: merge with failing tests or reduced critical-path coverage.
- Why: layered tests protect reliability and delivery speed.

## Opinionated Defaults

- Backend tests live in app-level `tests/` directories.
- Frontend tests live in co-located `__tests__/` folders.
- Test names should describe behavior and outcome.
- Canonical gate definitions live in `quality-gates.mdc`.

## Exceptions

- Temporary reduced coverage can be accepted only with:
  - documented waiver scope,
  - target date for remediation,
  - tracked issue for restoration.

## Acceptance Checks

- CI enforces tests, lint/type checks, and coverage threshold.
- Critical user journeys have explicit test coverage.
- New modules include at least one happy-path and one failure-path test.

## Examples

```python
# ✅ GOOD - Backend test
def test_create_resource_requires_authentication(client):
    response = client.post("/api/v1/resources/1/records", json={})
    assert response.status_code == 401
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Frontend test
describe('ResourceForm', () => {
  it('shows validation error when title is empty', async () => {
    const result = await submitForm({ title: '' });
    expect(result.errors).toContain('Title is required');
  });
});
```
